Analysis of Main Target Image
• Block Count & Layers  
  – There are 6 total blocks, arranged in three vertical “layers.”  
  – Layer 1 (bottom): Four blocks side‐by‐side in two rows.   
     1) Two yellow half‐cylinders at the front, touching each other.  
     2) One green cube (left) and one blue cube (right) directly behind the half‐cylinders.  
  – Layer 2 (middle): A single yellow rectangular bar spanning across the tops of the green and blue cubes.  
  – Layer 3 (top): A red arch‐shaped block centered on and resting atop the yellow bar, with its curved opening facing forward.  

Block Dictionary Selections  
To match shape, color, and orientation exactly (no rotations allowed), the following pieces are used:  
• Red arch: Index 2  
• Yellow rectangular bar: Index 9  
• Green cube: Index 7  
• Blue cube: Index 6  
• Yellow half‐cylinders (x2): Index 12 (twice)  

Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order  
{  
  Step1: Move block with index 7   (place the green cube)  
  Step2: Move block with index 6   (place the blue cube to the right of green)  
  Step3: Move block with index 12  (place first yellow half‐cylinder in front of green)  
  Step4: Move block with index 12  (place second yellow half‐cylinder in front of blue)  
  Step5: Move block with index 9   (place yellow bar atop the green and blue cubes)  
  Step6: Move block with index 2   (place red arch on top, curved side facing front)  
}
